value.title: Mike Pence is starting a podcast 'to share the good news of conservatism'
value.excerpt: The podcast marks just one of the latest ventures Pence is taking on after departing the Trump administration.

value.title: Harris flexes power as Senate tiebreaker
value.excerpt: Early Friday morning, Vice President Kamala Harris did something Joe Biden never did in his eight years as vice president -- cast a tie-breaking vote.

value.title: Illinois judge finds Trump hotel in Chicago liable for violating environmental laws
value.excerpt: The hotel has been sucking in millions of gallons of Chicago River water for its air-conditioning systems, without renewing a permit to do so.

value.title: Transgender Navy SEAL: Biden order 'going to give a lot of other individuals that chance to finally be themselves'
value.excerpt: When Navy SEAL Ashley Nefzger heard rumblings that President Joe Biden could sign an executive order to repeal a Trump-era ban on most transgender Americans joining the military, she was cautiously hopeful.

value.title: Biden says 'no need' for Trump to receive intel briefings: 'What impact does he have?'
value.excerpt: President Biden said he didn’t think his predecessor should receive intelligence briefings, as is standard for former presidents.

value.title: 'People are hurting,' Biden says as jobs report spurs stimulus push
value.excerpt: After weak jobs data showed the U.S. labor market recovery is stalling, President Joe Biden and his economic team on Friday hammered home the same message in meetings, interviews and television appearances: It's time to get more money out to the economy.

value.title: Hunter Biden still ‘working to unwind’ investment in Chinese firm
value.excerpt: President Joe Biden’s son Hunter maintains a holding in a Chinese investment firm, though the White House says he is "working to unwind his investments."

value.title: Pence's plans post-Trump administration take shape
value.excerpt: Former Vice President Mike Pence's post-Trump administration life is now starting to take shape. He's planning to host a new podcast and will be joining two conservative think tanks. Pence will be launching a podcast with Young America's Foundation,

value.title: Pro-Trump GOP chair steps down in Ohio, may seek Senate seat
value.excerpt: An Ohio Republican linked closely to Donald Trump has stepped down as the party’s chair, a signal of her interest in running for the U.S. Senate seat being left by the GOP’s Rob Portman

value.title: Biden administration likely going back to 'good old days' of Iran nuclear deal: McFarland
value.excerpt: The Biden administration is likely to look to go back to the "good old days" by renegotiating the Iran nuclear deal, former Deputy National Security Advisor K.T. McFarland told "America Reports" Friday.

value.title: ‘Stunning hypocrisy’ for Biden administration to push back against the CDC’s approval to open schools: Farah
value.excerpt: The Biden administration is hypocritical for appearing to dismiss the Center for Disease Control's guidance for reopening schools, former Trump White House Director of Strategic Communications Alyssa Farah said on Friday.

value.title: Biden: Rescue plan, 'answer to crisis we are in'
value.excerpt: President Joe Biden says the rescue plan he is pushing forward in Congress is the "answer to the crisis we are in." (Feb. 5)

value.title: Why Joe Biden's faith-based 'equity' agenda is getting pushback from religious conservatives
value.excerpt: Joe Biden, only the second Catholic president, has brought to the White House a different approach to faith, personally and politically, than Trump's.

value.title: What of ‘Individual-1’? Feds’ Trump campaign case is ‘dead’
value.excerpt: Prosecutors have shown no signs of reopening the campaign finance investigation that sent Donald Trump’s former attorney Michael Cohen to prison even now that Trump has left the White House

value.title: Fact check: Letter thanking President Trump was not written by Rush Limbaugh
value.excerpt: Social media users have been sharing a letter online attributed to conservative radio personality Rush Limbaugh that thanks former President Donald J. Trump for the past four years.

value.title: Angel dad slams Joe Biden's immigration orders: 'Insanity on steroids'
value.excerpt: A California father, whose son was killed in a car accident with an illegal immigrant slammed President Joe Biden’s move to halt deportations of undocumented migrants on Friday, calling the administration's actions “insanity on steroids.”

value.title: Lawyers Call Trump's First Amendment Defense 'Legally Frivolous'
value.excerpt: Taking aim at a key plank of the former president’s impeachment defense, the lawyers argue that the constitutional protections do not apply to an impeachment proceeding.

value.title: Biden administration’s CBP revives ‘catch and release’ policy at border amid COVID concerns
value.excerpt: A perfect storm of events has the Biden administration’s Customs and Border Protection on its heels in parts of Texas.

value.title: Pence will be ‘very active’ in 2022 elections amid new partnerships with conservative groups: ex-VP's adviser
value.excerpt: Pence announced he is joining the Heritage Foundation as a distinguished fellow and is also entering into a partnership with the conservative Young America’s Foundation.

value.title: Biden flying to Delaware despite CDC warnings to avoid travel
value.excerpt: President Biden is expected to travel to Delaware this weekend, in what will be his first out-of-town trip since taking office, despite warnings from the Centers of Disease Control and Prevention to avoid travel.

value.title: Biden set to accept more refugees after years of Trump restrictions
value.excerpt: U.S. President Joe Biden said on Thursday he plans to raise annual refugee admissions to 125,000 in the coming fiscal year, a more than eight-fold increase after former President Donald Trump slashed levels to historic lows.

value.title: Live Updates: Biden to Speak on Economy Hours After Senate Approves Relief Package
value.excerpt: President Biden and Vice President Harris plan to meet with House Democratic leaders Friday morning to discuss the stimulus package. The Senate approved Mr. Biden’s plan but knocked out the $15 minimum wage.

value.title: 'America is back' - Biden touts muscular foreign policy in first diplomatic speech
value.excerpt: U.S. President Joe Biden on Thursday promised a new era after the scattershot foreign policy of his predecessor, Donald Trump, declaring "America is back" on the global stage in his first diplomatic address as president.

value.title: Congressional Democrats propose up to $50,000 in debt cancelation, Biden not sold
value.excerpt: Congressional Democrats renewed calls Thursday for President Joe Biden to cancel up to $50,000 in federal student loans per individual.

value.title: Sen. Ben Sasse slams Nebraska GOP committee’s plans to censure him for criticizing Trump
value.excerpt: Sasse is the latest Republican to face censure or the threat of it from a state or local GOP for not supporting Trump.
